A member of HHS Secretary Alex Azar's security detail this week tested positive for coronavirus.

It is the first known instance of a staffer with regular proximity to the health secretary testing positive for the virus

text:
Opinion: Dems shouldn’t become complacent just because so many of Trump’s prior threats were empty. Nor should they start hollering about a fascistic takeover.

Instead, they should apply the lessons of the poker table to Trump’s latest political atrocity

name: politico
text:
Wall Street can deal with whoever wins the presidential election this fall.

What investors can’t stomach is a rapid descent into banana republic-style chaos, in which the result is either unclear for months or Trump loses but refuses to leave office
https://t.co/yIPtrzMcJu
